review_id: I've been to Fika a number of times, and it is always excellent!! Great selection of coffee, tea, and other drink options, and an excellent choice of snacks. The place is always clean and has great customer service. The best part of Fika is the atmosphere - it's the perfect coffee shop to talk with friends or to study quietly at a table. It's always busy and yet there is enough seating, I've never had trouble finding a table. My fellow customers have been friendly - Fika has built a great community of loyal customers over the years. 5 out of 5 stars for every visit!

review_id: Wonderful coffee. Really nice staff. Great ambiance. Wood paneling and earth tones help give the dowtown Parker staple a rustic but welcoming feel. Usually, there is plenty of seating, though weekends can be hopping/quite busy. It's probably the best coffee in town, yet somehow still keeps some of the best prices as well. A variety of fantastic looking pastries and other foods are offered as well.

review_id: Maybe it could be 4 stars. But people got my hopes up, saying this place has great coffee drinks. Tastes like Nescafe to me. I asked husband to order me an iced latte, basically (wishing I could order a caramel latte, but they don't have flavors here). He could have asked for it wrong though, since I received something BLENDED with ice instead. Basically a milky coffee blended with ice. Somewhat sweet. It wasn't DISTASTEFUL, mind you, just nothing outstanding. Good thing I didn't come on a busy day, where usually people wait an hr to get in. We also ordered food. My husband loved his Milanesa (chicken) and my chorizo con huevos was simply ok. Not bad, not great. The prices were reasonable. The bathrooms smelly, and water in the bathroom doesn't always work, apparently. This place doesn't live up to the hype. Kids loved their hotcakes. We went to the one at Independencia 1187, Centro Historico 91700 Veracruz, Ver. But I cannot seem to get the exact review spot for this location.

review_id: Several locals recommended this place.  Unfortunately the food was not great. We had one of each Panucho. The only one I liked was the dog fish, and I love Panuchos and have had great ones in Merida and other places. The scrambled eggs were not very good, and the beans were literally ice cold like they had taken them out of the refrigerator. My wife's molletes were not good either. The server was okay, but I had to get up to get my check.  Another server had to help us on one occasion and it wasn't very busy.

review_id: They were so nice, professional and super patient. It was my first time in there and I didn't know what I wanted but they helped me make a great decision.  They are better than Starbucks which is saying something. Next time I'm in Paris I will definitely be in for their awesome treats and wonderful coffee. They had variety of beautiful yummy danishes, fruit cup, kolaches and so many other things to choose from in addition to coffee.  I loved the vibe and lay out. They were very welcoming. I love how they had sleeves or coverings for the plastic ware to easily slide off when you're ready for them. I would definitely recommend this place to any and everyone traveling to Paris, Texas.

review_id:
I was sitting at my daughter's softball game and decided I needed a water. However the concession stand didn't take credit cards. I walked over to the coffee truck and picked up a cup of Joe. I was just chatting with the workers about the concession not taking CCs. No matter, I walked back to my seat and one of the gentlemen walked over to me and handed me a water. He had purchased it with his own money and walked it over to me.

Not only is the tasty, the service is spectacular. Lots of love to this coffee shop. Next time I'm in town I'll be sure to stop by the shop.

review_id:
Another update- tried to give them one last chance.  Ordered a breve, received a steamed milk. The Marilyn Manson look alike swore that's what a breve is. You are wrong. A breve is equal parts espresso and steamed half and half. Come on, educate yourself on what should be a basic coffee drink. What a joke.

Change in management? What happened to the very sweet guy that worked here, made incredible coffee and always had a smile?  The last 5 times we've been here the staff is very rude, the coffee is always burnt and they always forget something.  Once, twice...I'll chalk it up to a bad day. 5 times, come on! If you hate your job, quit. But why the attitude? It's certainly not inexpensive.  So many better options in Paris. I know I'm only one person,  but keep this up and the sentiment will spread.

This place opens 24 hours. It's like a grab-and-go with seatings but no real utensil nor plates. Everything was plastic and disposible.

French desserts in the refrigerator are great deals! They also have delicious french bakery ready made. I like their bakery and sweets and think that they're well made and justify the Vegas price.

Staff was not very friendly though.

review_id: I recently visited a coffee shop in my town and I was pleasantly surprised by the experience. The atmosphere was warm and inviting, with comfortable seating and a variety of coffee and tea options. The barista was friendly and knowledgeable, walking me through the menu and offering suggestions for my beverage. The coffee was delicious and served quickly. The overall experience was enjoyable and I would definitely recommend this coffee shop to anyone looking for an inviting and satisfying cup of coffee.

review_id:
Hope you get in on the membership, or you may not be serviced.

Waited patiently for over 20 minutes, while one person behind the counter tried to get everyone handled quickly. I finally get up to get the food and order a coffee,  but then 3 people came into line next to me, which is the "membership" line,  so I was not first any longer.  In addition to having to wait after those in the next line,  now conducted in front of me, once anyone else walked into the other line, i also had to wait... so I finally just decided to walk out without anything. This is not the kind of service I appreciate.

It is not the person's fault who was working, but a policy that you are served in the membership or may have to wait for an undetermined time.

What a bunch of baloney.

Maybe they have good food or even great coffee,  but I'm not going to find out.  I cannot ever recommend a place that treats people this way. I actually choose not to even try it.

review_id:
Before heading out of Kennebunkport and heading to Poland Spring Resort, we made a quick stop to Morning in Paris for Croissants and Coffee.
We love this place!
Croissants are buttery flaky and have a little crunch when you squeeze them.
Sign of croissant greatness!
Wife got spinach and feta croissant with o.j.
I got plain croissant with butter and raspberry preserves. Oh my God!!
Also got Honduran(light roast) coffee.
Black w a little Splenda( nice!)
Needless to say everything was exceptionally great! Someday we'll try the the crepes. They have a creperie in the back parking lot. We try to come here whenever in the area

review_id: I love everything about this Parisian Cafe located in Kennebunkport Maine! They have a wonderful selection of coffee, tea and specialty drinks plus their bakery items are so delicious! They also have the crepery next door that makes the BEST crepes this side of the Atlantic! The staff is also very friendly and they always accommodate for my service dog and even give him his own special pup cup when we visit :) They also offer Paris themed and local items to purchase and have a cozy indoor and outdoor sitting area. I really love it and always make it part of my daily routine when visiting.

review_id: Stopped in about an hour before closing on a Friday in early June. The guy at the counter was very friendly. We looked over the menu and decided on crepes. When e tried to order we were informed that they only do crepes on the weekend. Seems like it would make sense to write that on the crepe menu or take it down when they're not available. I ordered a sparkling water drink off the summer menu, it wasn't made as the description. The server used a raspberry flavor instead of blackberry and no lime slice was served with it. That was odd. My husband got blueberry crumble and I got a slice of quiche, both were good! Overall good service but needs work communicating 86-ed menu items. Nice seating areas both indoors and outdoors.

review_id: This was such a great recommendation!  We were glad we came here.  We were able to sit outside on the patio, it was such a gorgeous day.  Keep in mind that this is a bakery, not full breakfasts.  It is a fabulous bakery with many options.  Sadly they were out of ham and cheese croissants, which several people were asking for, and if we wanted a crepe (which sounded delicious), we were told we have to go outside to another building where they are made, and we can bring it back to this building to eat.  That sounded like extra work for us, so we all ordered a bakery item.  Very very busy place, but cute and clean!

review_id:
Morning  can be very busy! I was short on time so I had to leave the line. Pastries looked so good. So many choices for coffee  and tea !
I came back  for lunch because the Jazzy Peach  Tea, served lemonade style, with peach  coffee syrup sounded good ! It is! No small size available. I had a chicken  salad croissant  with almonds and cranberries. Needs more filling, but, the croissant wasn't hard or tough. Good texture!
Window and outdoor seating, WiFi and gifts available. AC inside. Friendly service. Cashless payment only. Touchless payment available.
I recommend a visit!

review_id: Cutest Brazilian cafe we stumbled into after a boat excursion at the piers. Had the most amazing salad with boiled eggs and a lemon vinaigrette. Ate every bite. And finished with a stuffed chocolate chip cookie, heavenly.

review_id:

review_id: Breakfast was great! No flavored lattes, but the coffee was good! The croissant sanwhich is their "breakfast sandwich."  This sandwich has their house sauce, which has horseradish in it. Indoor seating is limited.

review_id: Discovered this bakery while staying around the corner. Service is five stars, food is five stars, coffee is five stars. I have also had the avocado toast & went back multiple days in a row for the dulce de leche latte. Bacon egg and cheese sandwich is one of the best ever- hot, bacon bites off & the cheese is perfectly melted. Cheese bread is a must try too - 3 different kinds (everything, original and jalapeno). They do have a happy hour where you can purchase a dozen cheese bites for $10.00.

review_id: I had a DRIP coffee and a PB "cookie". Coffee was superb, and you get free refills!  The cookie was good, not great. It was more like a protein cookie, very dense, not very sweet. I would definitely go back for the coffee and ambiance, but would try a different food item. The ambiance is just lovely, a relaxing environment where you can read, study or quietly chat with a friend. UPDATE: Stopped in again today. Drip coffee still GREAT, but tried the apple cinnamon muffin....pretty sure it's not homemade by Aldea. Tasted store bought and a few days old. I guess I'll just stick to coffee when I go. I haven't tried ALL the food items, so maybe I'm missing out on a hidden gem, but it's 0/2 for the items I DID try. Definitely go for the coffee and vibes, though! UPDATE #2: Ok, I went back for my 3rd and last morning in GH. I tried the Cafe Miel and the Cherry Pistachio Biscotti.....YES!!!  I finally found a food item I liked and the Cafe Miel. Amazing!   The barista did tell me that the biscotti and CC cookie were made in-house.  My last trip to Aldea did not disappoint and I will be back (in a few years) when I'm back in town. Wish I had a coffee shop like Aldea within walking distance from my home! It's just lovely!

Service in atmosphere were 5 / 5! But, as for the food/coffee.. I will definitely choose something different from the menu next time.

I grabbed the Samoa Latte - as much as I love Samoa cookies, I didn't like it so much as a coffee. The flavor of the coffee was masked by the caramel and coconut syrup & just didn't give me a normal coffee kick.

Crepe was beautifully done, but I'm sticking to a 3/5 for flavor. I still ATE IT ALL! It was okay.

Such a cute spot in an upcoming neighborhood of McKinney! I'll definitely be back to try something else.

review_id:
Killebrew Coffeeshop - Great Coffee and Outstanding Service!

During a recent business trip, I visited Killebrew Coffeeshop in search of a good morning coffee. Despite the long line, the service was quick and efficient. I also had the pleasure of trying their outstanding ginger molasses cookie, which was a real treat. The latte I ordered was very well-made and hit the spot.

What really stood out, however, was the exceptional service. The staff was able to handle a group of unruly party guests while still providing great service to the rest of us. The customer service at Killebrew is truly top-notch.

I would highly recommend Killebrew Coffeeshop to anyone in the area looking for a great cup of coffee and exceptional customer service.

Killebrew Coffeeshop - Great Coffee and Outstanding Service!

During a recent business trip, I visited Killebrew Coffeeshop in search of a good morning coffee. Despite the long line, the service was quick and efficient. I also had the pleasure of trying their outstanding ginger molasses cookie, which was a real treat. The latte I ordered was very well-made and hit the spot.

What really stood out, however, was the exceptional service. The staff was able to handle a group of unruly party guests while still providing great service to the rest of us. The customer service at Killebrew is truly top-notch.

I would highly recommend Killebrew Coffeeshop to anyone in the area looking for a great cup of coffee and exceptional customer service.
response_from_owner_text: Wow, thank you so much for the amazing review, Alfons!  We truly appreciate your feedback and are so happy to hear you enjoyed everything. We hope to see you back at Killebrew soon!

review_id:
Mornings in Paris offers an expansive menu of coffee options paired with a traditional European-style morning cafe food selection, creating an exceptional local shop experience that is distinguished by its remarkable speed of service.

Upon our visit, my wife and I were delighted to sample an array of offerings, including the ham and cheese croissant, blueberry cream cheese croissant, and spinach croissant. Each selection surpassed our expectations and left an indelible impression. The croissants, in particular, transported me back to my travels in France and Belgium, evoking the authentic taste and texture reminiscent of those European pastries. I cannot emphasize enough how excellent these choices were, making them a highly recommended option for anyone visiting Mornings in Paris.

While the seating options are somewhat limited within the cafe, they do offer a charming outdoor seating area, which provides a pleasant atmosphere for enjoying your meal and coffee.

Speaking of coffee, Mornings in Paris excels in this department as well. Their cold brew, cappuccino, and Americano, all prepared using European-styled machines, were nothing short of excellent. The commitment to crafting high-quality coffee beverages is readily apparent, and it significantly enhances the overall dining experience.

In sum, Mornings in Paris delivers a delightful fusion of gourmet coffee offerings and delectable European-style morning cafe fare. From the exquisite croissants that evoke the essence of continental bakeries to the expertly brewed coffee, this establishment offers an exceptional and highly recommended culinary experience. Please be mindful of the limited indoor seating, but the charming outdoor area provides a wonderful alternative for savoring your coffee and pastries.

review_id: Ordered a latte and chocolate croissant.  Latte was nice.  We'll balanced and flavorful.  The croissant not so much.  Didn't ask us if we wanted it warmed up.  Assumed they would but it came out cold.  Asked for it to be heated and it came back within a minute.  What does that tell you?  Microwave.  And sure enough the croissant was chewy like it had been nuked.  Not great.
review_text: Ordered a latte and chocolate croissant.  Latte was nice.  We'll balanced and flavorful.  The croissant not so much.  Didn't ask us if we wanted it warmed up. response_from_owner_text:
Our croissants are made and baked fresh in the morning, never frozen. We absolutely do not recommend to warm them up, it is a sacrilege and something we leave to Starbucks... we will remind our staff that they should ALWAYS tell our guests that the "warmed up" croissant will be a poor experience. It destroys flavors, layers and consistency.  Come experience a croissant at room
Temperature, not "cold", that's how it is  meant to be enjoyed.

review_id: My wife and I went for brunch on a Saturday. I ordered the croque-mister which was pretty good. Savory with a balanced taste. My wife took the egg Benedict with salmon. The salmon was very good and we like the amount of sauce in it. The English muffin  in the Benedict however felt a little over done and hard to cut. Otherwise pretty darn good. Their side of potatoes were also lovely.  We also tried the game and cheese croissant which was pretty good as well. Definitely recommended. I also took something, I forgot the name, but it was like a strawberry cheese cake. It was tasty as well and would definitely try again.

review_id: Today I decided to try the Pain au chocolat, or chocolatine as I knew them from my childhood summer trips to the south of France, from the best rated Mercer Island bakeries. I am here to say this fellow conquered my palate, was beautifully flaky and the taste of delicious butter was in every single bite. The filling was amazing, the chocolate was not too sweet but just perfect, it melted in my mouth after each bite. The whole combination was splendid, defectless. Highly recommend it. As for the location, I wasn't tempted enough to stay. However it was clean and filled with happy costumers.

review_id:
This place is overpriced and they have bad service. Spend time to go there today and buy a Lorraine quiche to take to my child for lunch, the young lady that packed it to go packed it in a container with small holes on the bottom... there was salad with balsamic in there as well, the container leaked through, also, the top of the to go container wasn't staying properly closed, so I took it back leaking as it was. I asked for a manager, the lady said there was no one there and that they usually aren't there and didn't provide me with anyone I could call. She also accused me of saying the F word, which I didn't, I said "freaking leaked" she may have heard the F word but either way, she packed my food in the container and I felt like she didn't need to get into an argument with a paying costumer that just wasted they're time. I asked for a refund and she gave it to me. That being said, I got a bad taste from the service that was provided and I doubt I will be returning to this place.

Over Priced and Overworked Staff. This is not the "Paris" experience I desired.

review_id:
This part of Arkansas has ties to the movie True Grit. It is based on a novel written by an Arkansan. The setting is in Arkansas, not too far from Paris, and a famous Arkansan starred in it. While you are setting their sipping your coffee, see if you can figure all that out. The title and the association of the movie to the area, makes a catchy name for the coffee shop.
The coffee is outstanding. The service is small town Arkansas friendly. It is an attractive, relaxing environment to waste a morning in and enjoy some of the best coffee you will ever have. My wife is an expert and coffee epicurean (aka Coffee Snob.) She rated her coffee drink this morning as "better than I can make at home." That means it is damn good. Me, no coffee expert, but I enjoyed my cup too. She went with an iced hazel nut latte. It was perfectly balanced. The coffee was not overwhelmed by the hazel nut flavoring, nor too sweet. I had already had two cups of coffee this morning. I didn't need more caffeine. I ordered a decaf mocha with a twist.   I asked for non-fat milk and no whipped cream. The young lady asked if I would like to try it with unsweetened dark chocolate.  It was amazing. It is now my new coffee drink.
FYI - I hated the movie.

For other reviews laced with superfluous, time-wasting inessential information, sarcastic diatribe, and subjective opinion, follow Spike S. on Yelp and Spike Speedwell on Google

review_id:
Visited Paris, Arkansas yesterday to get out and about. Dropped in at the fairgrounds for a craft fair, then a few shops downtown, and after that... coffee!

I have seen a few folks post about @truegritgrounds but had not been until yesterday.  Their shop is right on the square in downtown Paris and is comfy and cute.  The staff were friendly and efficient. The kiddos got mochas and I had an Americano - we played some trivia while we sipped on our drinks.

Downtown Paris is a hidden gem!

 I certainly hope you will come back soon so we can earn your love!

Jason

review_id:
Jack's Java in Paris, TN has become a cherished regular spot for our coffee cravings. The coffee always hits the spot, consistently delivering a delicious and satisfying experience. However, it was a recent visit with my daughters that truly highlighted the exceptional kindness and thoughtfulness of the staff.

My daughters walked down to Jack's Java to enjoy a smoothie and a chocolate milk. To my surprise, my youngest daughter ran back with sheer excitement, sharing a heartwarming story. She recounted how the lady behind the counter, without even being asked, kindly offered her a glass of water alongside her chocolate milk. The lady's explanation melted my heart: "I always need some water after I finish my chocolate milk." It's the little things that can make the biggest differences in life.

This small act of genuine care and consideration made my daughters' day, and it warms my heart to know that Jack's Java goes above and beyond to make their customers feel valued and appreciated. The kindness extended towards my girls truly made a lasting impression.

Beyond their exceptional customer service, Jack's Java continues to impress with their tasty treats and inviting atmosphere. It's a place where you can not only satisfy your coffee cravings but also feel the warmth of a welcoming community.

If you're in Paris, TN, make sure to visit Jack's Java. You'll not only be treated to delicious beverages and delightful treats, but you'll also experience the genuine kindness and thoughtfulness that sets this coffee shop apart. A heartfelt thank you to the staff at Jack's Java for making my daughters' day extra special!

I had an Americano and it was one of the best I've had.
Good coffee starts with good beans and I think Le Paris has found great beans.
I distort the pastries but they looked amazing.
To the owners, please consider have some vegan pastries available.

review_id: OMG! This place is amazing. A hidden gem in the middle of Vegas. A 5-star well deserved!!! I got a tasty double espresso and a fresh almond chocolate pastry. The atmosphere was nice and cozy with cool jazz playing. The place had several customers and we all struck up a nice conversation. The staff was super nice and the place is really clean. Thanks so much for a great time and see ya all again soon! Happy customer, Michael

review_id: Came here in on Saturday AM because of the reviews on google. It's a small cafe. Ordered 3 breakfast menu, two coffee and two hot chocolate. Omelette, croissant ham sandwich, and french toast. All taste good. I wish there are more french toast(mine came with 4 thin triangles of toast). My breakfast cost $44 and additional tips.

review_id: I have tried their tiramisu at fashion show mall at their stand alone bakery there. It was sweet but very well put together. I expected it to be soggy like most tiramisus are but it was the perfect ratio. I loved it so much i ordered a tiramisu cake for my brothers birthday. I appreciate the effort and will come back soon.

review_id: This was my first time visiting and I'll definitely be going back. Atmosphere alone is amazing but what really topped it off was the service. I was helped Bella and she was great. I had mentioned I didn't know what to get and she asked me the type of things I liked. She suggested the nutty cookie and it was delicious. She not only listened but also showed interest in what I was saying, which is rare. She was lovely and went above and beyond to make my visit nice !!

review_id: Love this place!! So pretty! Delicious coffee flavors! Totally fun items in the boutique! And spectacular service and atmosphere! Definitely going back again!!!

review_id:
Brand new cute coffee bar in town. Offering teas which can be ordered in tea pots, coffee , non coffee items with a small selection of danishes, muffins, macaroons to enjoy with your choice of drink. Order to go or stay and enjoy your coffee in a mug.
Bright, relaxing vibes with some hand made small business items to shop if you wish.
Be sure to follow them on Instagram @Bosschiccoffeebar to see when they have pop up event where they may stay open later. Support local small businesses.
Bonus with a tree swing or front.

review_id:
i don't write reviews but this place absolutely deserves it. if you love all things pink, cutesy, and adorable, this is where you go. the amount of sanrio merch had me overjoyed and i obviously bought a my melody sticker sheet! cafe wise, i ordered the cinnamoroll latte from their sanrio menu and my husband ordered a plain, iced americano with no cream or flavor. my latte was lovely and not too sweet. my husband loved his coffee and he's extremely picky about it! the lady up front was so sweet and she gave us a loyalty card! also some lil thingies for their halloween event on 10/28!! overall it was lovely, atmosphere was my dream, and i will absolutely return and be a frequent customer. thank you guys for the amazing vibes!!!
**ALSO!!! they currently have a sale where all pink items get a discount for breast cancer awareness month!!!!**

I love this wonderful place in Patos!!! Absolutely everything here at Aroma cafe is made with great quality!! If I could rate it 1000 I would, because it can't be that good!!
I had a coffee with lemon which was such an incredible experience, I never imagined it would be delicious!! Amen!!

review_id:
Simpatica e rapida a atendente.

Local bem arejado, aberto, entra bastante luz natural (o que me agrada bastante)

"Fica meio escondido " pra quem nao conhece ou nao esta procurando de forma especifica, mas vale a pena procurar.

Cardapio bem diversificado e precos de acordo com a qualidade. Caro nao quer dizer bom e barato nao quer dizer ruim, mas qualidade exige preco justo.

Friendly and quick attendant.

Well ventilated, open space with plenty of natural light (which I really like)

"It's a little hidden" for those who don't know it or aren't looking for it specifically, but it's worth looking for.

Very diverse menu and prices according to quality. Expensive doesn't mean good and cheap doesn't mean bad, but quality demands a fair price.

review_id: I absolutely love this coffee shop and if you want really good coffee, an amazing service, then take the extra five minutes to walk away from Starbucks over to the Branson Landing! They have all sorts of breakfast, assortments healthy treats, juices, an amazing coffee, not to mention amazing service! Upon coming back my third time this trip I found out that it was 2  really sweet sisters that own the shop who both served me the day before, and I had to leave a review this is a must visit!

review_id:
Finally, a place in Branson for coffee snobs to call home. They serve the traditional Macchiato. Need I say more?

If you're particular about your coffee, you'll be delighted by Zo's. Delicious pastries and excellent espresso. I'll be here often.

review_id: I bought $30 in coffee and they kindly added a nominal 3% charge for using a credit card without telling me. No notice whatsoever and it just shows up on the receipt after the fact. I guess $30 for a few coffees just doesn't quite cover their massive overhead costs....  Nice place, but beware a bit scammy.

review_id: I went in here with high hopes but the coffee was mediocre, if that. I definitely want to see a small business strive, however, for the price you pay for the quality you get, I wish I would have listened to everyone else and stuck with somewhere else. Contrary to other reviews, service was not exceptional and staff were not super friendly nor did the environment feel welcoming. Not a place I would recommend for coffee at least :/ Hoping it was just an off day and that their business succeeds on the landing!!

review_id:
One of the worst experiences I've had. When I walked up, both baristas were chatting with, what I thought, was a customer. Turns out it was a fellow employee on break. He left, they still didn't acknowledge me. I had to ask, are you closed? before they acknowledged me, but then they only said, yes, and then, after a few moments more, we'll be with you in a minute.
The girl asked me 2 or 3 times if I wanted whipped cream. Clearly, she wasn't listening to me.
If you don't want to work and just want to chat with your friends then what are they paying you for!?
They only have 16 or 20 oz drink sizes.
And my hot chocolate wasn't even good. Tasted like a Swiss Miss packet and wasn't creamy.

review_id:
Uma cafeteria nova em Patos de Minas com um excelente atendimento e muitos cafes diferentes e gostosos.

O atendimento e todo feito por voce mesmo, na recepcao da cafeteria em uma tela onde voce mesmo escolhe os produtos, ja coloca seu nome, posiciona se vai consumir ou levar (detalhe que esta cafeteria tem um formato de pegar e levar - tendo poucas mesas para consumir no local, mas e possivel sim consumir la).

Cafe sai rapido e atendimento top. Recomendo conhecer.

review_translated_text:
A new cafe in Patos de Minas with excellent service and many different and delicious coffees.

The service is all done by you, at the cafeteria reception on a screen where you choose the products yourself, enter your name, decide whether you are going to consume or take away (detail that this cafe has a grab and go format - with few tables to consume on site, but it is possible to consume there).

Coffee comes out quickly and service is top notch. I recommend getting to know it.
